The paper deals with the problem of testing uniformity of an unknown distribution, which is a fundamental problem in distribution testing. This problem is relevant in various areas of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), computational complexity (cs.CC), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
